headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 21 rebounds and nine assists, Monte Morris made four free throws in the final 11.5 seconds, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Detroit Pistons 110-105 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's 28 points, 21 rebounds leads Nuggets past Pistons

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 24 points and matched his career high with 12 assists, and Gary Trent Jr. scored a season-best 32 for the Toronto Raptors in a 125-113 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam and Trent Jr. lead Raptors past Hornets, 125-113

headlines.description: — The Los Angeles Clippers are the NBA's new comeback kings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kennard scores 7 in final 9 seconds as Clippers stun Wizards

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid is dominating opponents nightly — and he doesn’t plan on stopping anytime soon.
— Jayson Tatum scored 36 points and Jaylen Brown had 30 points and 10 rebounds before both rested the entire fourth quarter as the Boston Celtics routed the Sacramento Kings 128-75 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown lead Celtics in 128-75 laugher over Kings

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis' knee looked fine leaping high to slam down a lob pass from LeBron James on the game's first possession.
headlines.shortLinkText: James has 33, Lakers beat Nets 106-96 in Davis' return

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray and Jakob Poeltl combined for 37 points in three quarters to help the San Antonio Spurs coast to a 134-104 victory over the Houston Rockets Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Poeltl power Spurs to easy 134-104 win over Rockets

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson is playing a few more minutes now, making pretty passes and knocking down shots from all spots on the floor. Sure, everyone told him to expect rust for a while — and he's not having it.

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 40 points, including 14 points in the fourth quarter, and the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 109-107 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards has 40 points, Timberwolves down Blazers 109-107
